 {"id":"bd-3dh.6","title":"Implement Actionable view mode for execution plan visualization","description":"Go's Actionable view (a key) shows the execution plan as parallel tracks of work. List pane shows tracks with their items, detail pane shows track reasoning, dependencies, and estimated timeline. IMPLEMENTATION: (1) Add Actionable variant to ViewMode enum. (2) On a key from main, compute execution plan. (3) List pane: render tracks as groups, each showing track ID, item count, estimated duration. (4) Detail pane: selected track shows items in order, blocker chains, reason text. (5) Add j/k navigation within and between tracks. (6) Wire in help text. DEPENDS ON: Plan reasoning fields (bd-1ru.6) for full track explanations. ACCEPTANCE: a key enters actionable view. Tracks are navigable. Detail shows plan info.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:59:41.441511889Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:58:52.706668394Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:58:52.704180846Z","close_reason":"Implemented Actionable view mode: 'a' key toggles view, computes execution plan via triage+plan, j/k navigates tracks (List) and items (Detail), shows track IDs/reasons/items with scores/unblocks/claim commands. All 727 tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3dh.6","depends_on_id":"bd-1ru.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:04:34.062068996Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3dh.6","depends_on_id":"bd-3dh","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:59:41.441511889Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":33,"issue_id":"bd-3dh.6","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Actionable view: displays the execution plan as a visual timeline/kanban with tracks, showing which issues to work on in what order. Uses plan reasoning (bd-1ru.6) to show WHY each track is ordered that way. BLOCKED BY bd-1ru.6.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:08:13Z"},{"id":87,"issue_id":"bd-3dh.6","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"TESTING REQUIREMENT: This task is NOT complete until it includes: (1) at least one unit test constructing BvrApp with test data, sending the relevant key event, and asserting the resulting state change, (2) an edge case test with empty/minimal data to ensure no panic. Follow existing test patterns in tui.rs.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:37:42Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-3dh.7","title":"Implement Attention view mode with attention-ranked label filtering","description":"Go's \\! key opens an alerts panel showing active alerts (cycle warnings, stale issues, blocking cascades) with severity levels (critical/warning/info). Users can dismiss alerts and filter by severity. IMPLEMENTATION: (1) Add Alerts variant to ViewMode enum. (2) On \\! key, compute alerts via analysis::alerts module (already exists). (3) List pane: alerts sorted by severity (critical first), showing icon + summary. (4) Detail pane: full alert details with affected issues and remediation steps. (5) Add severity filter (c/w/i keys for critical/warning/info). (6) Add dismiss functionality (d key to mark alert as seen). (7) Show alert count badge in main view status bar. ACCEPTANCE: \\! key shows alerts. Severity filtering works. Alert count shows in status bar.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:59:44.469145615Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T03:24:15.981672754Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T03:24:15.979276067Z","close_reason":"Implemented Attention view mode: ! key toggles, computes label attention scores via label_intel, list shows ranked labels (rank/label/score/reason table), detail shows full breakdown (counts, PageRank sum, staleness/block/velocity factors, affected issues). j/k navigation. 4 unit tests. 468 lib tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3dh.7","depends_on_id":"bd-3dh","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:59:44.469145615Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3dh.7","depends_on_id":"bd-ybj.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:04:45.225705575Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":34,"issue_id":"bd-3dh.7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Alerts view: shows issues needing attention, grouped by severity (critical/warning/info). Sources: stale issues, cycle members, orphaned nodes, blocking bottlenecks. BLOCKED BY bd-ybj.5 (advanced insights for alert sources).","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:08:15Z"},{"id":53,"issue_id":"bd-3dh.7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"CORRECTION: Go does NOT have an 'Alerts' view. It has focusAttention (attention-ranked labels) in pkg/ui/model.go. The attention.go file implements attention-ranked label display, not severity-filtered alerts. Rename this view to Attention and implement attention-ranked label display matching Go's implementation. Also related: Go has --robot-alerts as a robot command which IS separate from the TUI attention view.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:33:01Z"},{"id":88,"issue_id":"bd-3dh.7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"TESTING REQUIREMENT: This task is NOT complete until it includes: (1) at least one unit test constructing BvrApp with test data, sending the relevant key event, and asserting the resulting state change, (2) an edge case test with empty/minimal data to ensure no panic. Follow existing test patterns in tui.rs.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:37:42Z"}]}
