 {"id":"bd-3dy","title":"Async Phase 2: background metric computation for large graphs","description":"WHAT: For graphs above a configurable size threshold, compute expensive metrics (betweenness centrality, eigenvector centrality) in a background thread while returning fast metrics (PageRank, k-core, degree) immediately. WHY: Go handles this via goroutines in pkg/analysis/analysis.go — expensive metrics compute in background while the TUI shows partial results. Our Rust engine blocks on all metrics before returning anything, which makes large graphs feel sluggish. This is lower priority because most real-world beads graphs are small (<1000 nodes), but it's important for the 'wow factor' on large repos. IMPLEMENTATION: Use std::thread::spawn (not async — we don't have a runtime and don't need one for CPU-bound work). GraphAnalyzer returns AnalysisResult with Option<T> for expensive metrics. TUI polls for completion and re-renders when background metrics arrive. Config system (bd-6gv) provides the size threshold. ACCEPTANCE: Fast metrics return in <100ms regardless of graph size. Expensive metrics fill in within seconds. TUI shows progress indicator while background computation runs. No unsafe code. DEPENDS ON: bd-6gv (config system for thresholds). PARENT: bd-3in","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:03:26.474517253Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T00:37:48.700574507Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3dy","depends_on_id":"bd-6gv","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:03:44.663067770Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":45,"issue_id":"bd-3dy","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"DESIGN: Two-phase result: AnalysisResult{fast: FastMetrics, slow: Option<SlowMetrics>}. FastMetrics: PageRank, degree, k-core (all O(V+E) or near). SlowMetrics: betweenness (O(VE)), eigenvector (iterative). TUI renders fast immediately, shows spinner for slow, re-renders on completion via channel notification. Thread join on app exit to prevent resource leak.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:09:24Z"},{"id":98,"issue_id":"bd-3dy","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"TESTING REQUIREMENT: This task is NOT complete until it includes inline unit tests. Config: test load/merge/default. Cache: test hit/miss/TTL/invalidation. Feedback: test round-trip/apply/corrupt-file. Async: test fast-return/eventual-complete.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:37:48Z"}]}
