+{"id":"bd-7oo.1.3.2","title":"Port static-host and offline-safe asset reference semantics","description":"Background:\\nHaving the right files on disk is not enough if the exported HTML and runtime still assume the wrong path, host, or CDN model.\\n\\nGoal:\\nMake the exported asset references behave correctly for offline and generic static-host deployment flows.","design":"Implementation expectations:\\n- Make HTML and runtime references work for offline usage and generic static hosts, not just the local dev flow.\\n- Eliminate implicit CDN assumptions and make pathing, routing, and relative reference behavior explicit.\\n- Add focused tests or fixtures for representative host/offline path semantics where practical.","acceptance_criteria":"- Asset references work under offline and generic static-host assumptions.\\n- No required viewer path still depends on an external CDN or a dev-only host layout.\\n- Focused checks make host/reference regressions easy to isolate.","notes":"This bead is specifically about host/offline semantics, which are easy to break even when all the right files exist.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":120,"created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:53.202155834Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T06:36:21.866400015Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T06:36:21.865556034Z","close_reason":"Added offline-safe asset reference verification: 3 new tests (no external URLs, all script/link refs resolve to inventory, CSP meta tag present). Updated parity contract: promoted offline-graph-runtime-pack, search-loader-assets, root-stylesheet, root-viewer-script from deferred/non-goal to must-have-now. Updated meta-title and local-bootstrap observers for canonical index.html semantics. 14 total viewer_assets tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["export-pages","frontend","legacy-port","parity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:53.202155834Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:56.451919222Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-7oo.1.3.3","title":"Port CSP, cache, and browser-runtime semantics for the exported viewer","description":"Background:\\nThe legacy bundle encoded browser-runtime assumptions such as CSP, caching, and worker or vendor runtime behavior that are easy to miss if asset parity is treated as a file-copy problem.\\n\\nGoal:\\nRestore the browser-runtime semantics that make the exported viewer safe and functional in real deployments.","design":"Implementation expectations:\\n- Restore the CSP, cache, and browser-runtime semantics that matter for the exported viewer to behave safely and predictably.\\n- Be explicit about worker, vendor, bootstrap, or script-loading behavior that affects deployed bundles.\\n- Add focused assertions for the runtime contract where deterministic checks are possible.","acceptance_criteria":"- The exported viewer honors the agreed CSP/cache/runtime contract.\\n- Browser-side bootstrap behavior remains compatible with the packaged asset model and static-host assumptions.\\n- Focused assertions make CSP/runtime regressions visible before the full export parity suite runs.","notes":"This bead prevents 'asset parity' from stopping at file counts while missing the actual browser-runtime contract.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":120,"created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:53.333569364Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:56.597327911Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["export-pages","frontend","legacy-port","parity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:53.333569364Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:56.597254042Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-7oo.1.4","title":"Port auxiliary export artifacts such as project health metadata and deploy-facing docs","description":"Background:\nLegacy Go export also emitted supporting artifacts that made the bundle usable in real deployment workflows: extra JSON like project health summaries, generated README content, and host-facing guidance or workflow material.\n\nGoal:\nRestore the deploy-facing and operations-facing artifacts that made legacy static export self-explanatory for GitHub Pages, Cloudflare Pages, and generic static hosts.","design":"Implementation expectations:\n- Identify which non-viewer artifacts are part of the real legacy export contract versus optional niceties.\n- Implement the minimum set that materially affects usability, deployment parity, and self-description of the exported bundle.\n- Avoid generating brittle boilerplate that is not validated anywhere.","acceptance_criteria":"- Rust export emits the agreed supplemental artifacts required by the contract.\n- Integration tests verify their presence and key content or invariants.\n- The bundle is more self-describing for future users and operators without depending on external docs.","notes":"Examples from the audit include project-health-style data and generated README or deployment-facing outputs. The exact set should be locked by the export contract bead rather than guessed ad hoc.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-07T23:41:51.485393882Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:58.293712418Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["docs","export-pages","legacy-port","parity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:41:51.485393882Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:00:07.513726785Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:57.737414259Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:57.884569119Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:58.027694160Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:58.163793468Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.3.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:58.293661844Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-7oo.1.5","title":"Build export unit, conformance, and integration coverage for full artifact parity","description":"Background:\nExport parity claims are easy to overstate unless they are backed by executable evidence. This task exists to make the export feature track falsifiable and stable over time before the shell-e2e layer is added.\n\nGoal:\nCreate or extend unit, integration, and conformance coverage so the Rust export surface can be verified against the artifact contract and key legacy behaviors.","design":"Implementation expectations: Add module-level tests for deterministic export logic such as schema shaping, config serialization, artifact classification, and edge cases where those helpers can be exercised without full process launches. Add integration tests for artifact presence, SQLite or config validity, offline asset invariants, and generated supplemental outputs. The suite should explicitly cover a happy-path export, a representative minimal or edge-case export, and clear negative-path assertions for missing or malformed artifacts or schema invariants. Reuse or extend reference fixtures where that reduces ambiguity. Make failures precise enough that future agents can identify which aspect of export parity regressed, and shape the test outputs so they can feed the later shell-e2e bead cleanly.","acceptance_criteria":"Export parity has explicit unit coverage for deterministic export logic and integration or conformance coverage for the full artifact matrix. The suite covers happy-path, representative edge-case, and negative regression scenarios, and fails when required artifacts or invariants are missing. Export parity can be validated with `rch` without manually inspecting the bundle.","notes":"This bead is the code-level closure mechanism for the export artifact track. It intentionally stops short of shell-e2e workflow coverage, which is handled by the companion export/pages e2e bead, but it must already make failures and artifact mismatches easy to diagnose.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":300,"created_at":"2026-03-07T23:41:51.664387972Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:59.203659604Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["export-pages","legacy-port","parity","tests","verification"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:41:51.664387972Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:13:41.596795594Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:58.680563365Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:58.813526278Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:58.939361307Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:59.066009160Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.3.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T21:58:59.203594552Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-7oo.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-7oo.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:41:55.270423907Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
